The paper deals with non-photorealistic rendering of images, which involves manipulating image features such as edges and texture to achieve a desired depiction of the scene. This falls under the category of computer graphics (cs.GR) and computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed approach involves a content-aware framework, which suggests the involvement of machine learning (cs.AI) and possibly deep learning (cs.LG) techniques. The paper also mentions applications such as detail exaggeration and image abstraction, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM).
